    "message": "The route module now imports a second, parallel data-access layer (`..db.item_service` providing `add_item`/`fetch_all_items`) alongside the existing `..db.repository` (`list_items`). The same module's GET handler reads through `repository` while the new POST handler writes through `item_service`, so a single route now depends on two duplicate data-access modules for the same `Item` aggregate. This is inappropriate cross-boundary coupling — the route layer is the only thing binding two competing persistence layers together, and the diff's own docstring labels it a \"duplicate data-access layer.\" Consolidate item persistence behind one repository (`repository.py`) and delete/merge `item_service`.",
